body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Running `prep -auto-top` on this Module:

```verilog
module meminit(
	output wire[10:0] m,
);
	reg [10:0] mem[1:0];
	initial begin
		mem[0][7:3] = 5'b10011;
		mem[0][3:2] = 2'b00;
		mem[0][1] = 1'b1;
	end
	assign m = mem[0];
endmodule
```

## Expected behavior

`mem[0]` should be set to `11'bxxx1001001x`

## Actual behavior

`mem[0]` is set to `11'b0000000001x`. The last line in the initial block seems to completely override the others.

`write_verilog` prints:
```verilog
module meminit(m);
  output [10:0] m;
  reg [10:0] mem [1:0];
  initial begin
    mem[0] = 11'b0000000001x;
  end
  assign m = mem[1'h0];
endmodule
```

